Bathyscaphe Trieste.label: Bathyscaphe Trieste

Brazilian aircraft carrier Minas Gerais.description: NAeL Minas Gerais was a Colossus-class aircraft carrier operated by the Marinha do Brasil from 1960 until 2001. Wikipedia

Bulgaria (ship).label: Bulgaria
Bulgaria (ship).description: Bulgaria was a class 785/OL800 Russian river cruise ship which operated in the Volga-Don basin. On 10 July 2011, Bulgaria sank in the Kuybyshev Reservoir of the Volga River near Syukeyevo, Kamsko-Ustyinsky ... Wikipedia

COSCO Guangzhou.label: COSCO Guangzhou
COSCO Guangzhou.description: COSCO Guangzhou is a container ship, and one of the largest currently in service. She was built for Cosco Ship Management in 2006 at the company's shipyards. Wikipedia

CSS Alabama.label: CSS Alabama
CSS Alabama.description: CSS Alabama was a screw sloop-of-war built in 1862 for the Confederate States Navy at Birkenhead, England by John Laird Sons and Company. Wikipedia

Costa Voyager.label: Costa Voyager
Costa Voyager.description: MS Costa Voyager îs a cruise ship that was sailing for Costa Crociere and was formerly owned by Royal Olympic Cruises and Ibero Cruises as Grand Voyager. Wikipedia

CSS Grampus.label: CSS Grampus
CSS Grampus.description: CSS Grampus was a stern-wheel river steamer built in 1856 at McKeesport, Pennsylvania, for civilian employment. Taken by the Confederate Army in early 1862, she served as a scout boat and transport on the Mississippi River. Wikipedia

Esmeralda (BE-43).label: Esmeralda (BE-43)
Esmeralda (BE-43).description: The Esmeralda is a steel-hulled four-masted barquentine tall ship of the Chilean Navy. Wikipedia

CSS Virginia.label: CSS Virginia
CSS Virginia.description: CSS Virginia was the first steam-powered ironclad warship built by the Confederate States Navy during the first year of the American Civil War; she was constructed as a casemate ironclad using the raised ... Wikipedia

France II.label: France II
France II.description: The France II was a French sailing ship and the second one of that name. She was the second largest commercial merchant sailing ship ever built. Wikipedia

French cruiser Colbert (1928).label: French cruiser Colbert
French cruiser Colbert (1928).description: The Colbert was a French heavy cruiser of the Suffren class, that saw service in World War II. She was named for Jean Baptiste Colbert. Wikipedia

French cruiser Colbert (C611).label: French cruiser Colbert
French cruiser Colbert (C611).description: Colbert was an anti-air cruiser, later transformed into a missile cruiser, of the French Navy. She was the sixth ship of the French Navy to be named after Jean-Baptiste Colbert. Wikipedia

French cruiser De Grasse.label: French cruiser De Grasse
French cruiser De Grasse.description: The De Grasse was an anti-aircraft cruiser of the French Navy. She was the first French vessel named in honour of François Joseph Paul, marquis de Grasetilly, comte de Grasse. She was involved in the nuclear test campaigns in Mururoa. Wikipedia

French cruiser Jeanne d'Arc (R97).label: French cruiser Jeanne d'Arc
French cruiser Jeanne d'Arc (R97).description: The Jeanne d'Arc (R97) was a helicopter cruiser of the French Navy. She was the third vessel of the French Navy named after Joan of Arc, a national heroine of France and saint of the Catholic Church ... Wikipedia

French cruiser Primauguet (1924).label: French cruiser Primauguet
French cruiser Primauguet (1924).description: Primauguet was a French Duguay-Trouin-class light cruiser built after World War I and destroyed by US naval gunfire from the battleship Massachusetts. She was named after the 15th century Breton captain Hervé de Portzmoguer, nicknamed "Primauguet". Wikipedia

French cruiser Tourville.label: French cruiser Tourville
French cruiser Tourville.description: The Tourville was a French Duquesne class heavy cruiser that served during World War II. Wikipedia

French destroyer Aconit (F65).label: French destroyer Aconit
French destroyer Aconit (F65).description: Aconit was a unique frigate built for the French Navy during the Cold War, in commission from 1973 until 1997. She was named after the corvette Aconit which fought in the Free French Naval Forces during World War II. Wikipedia

French frigate Sensible (1788).label: French frigate Sensible
French frigate Sensible (1788).description: Sensible was a 32-gun Magicienne-class frigate of the French Navy. The Royal Navy captured her in 1798 off Malta and took into service as HMS Sensible. She was lost in a grounding off Ceylon in 1802. Wikipedia

French ironclad Gloire.label: French ironclad Gloire
French ironclad Gloire.description: The French ironclad Gloire was the first ocean-going ironclad, launched in 1859. She was developed following the Crimean War, in response to new developments in naval gun technology, especially the ... Wikipedia

French submarine Surcouf (N N 3).label: French submarine Surcouf
French submarine Surcouf (N N 3).description: Surcouf was a French submarine ordered to be built in December 1927, launched on 18 October 1929, and commissioned in May 1934. Wikipedia

GTS Finnjet.label: GTS Finnjet
GTS Finnjet.description: GTS Finnjet was a cruiseferry, built in 1977 by Wärtsilä Helsinki, Finland for Finnlines traffic between Finland and Germany. Wikipedia

German aircraft carrier Graf Zeppelin.label: German aircraft carrier Graf Zeppelin

German cruiser Blücher.label: German cruiser Blücher
German cruiser Blücher.description: Blücher was the second of five Admiral Hipper class heavy cruisers of the German Kriegsmarine, built after the rise of the Nazi Party and the repudiation of the Treaty of Versailles. Wikipedia

German cruiser Köln.label: German cruiser Köln
German cruiser Köln.description: Köln was a light cruiser, the third member of the Königsberg class that was operated between 1929 and March 1945, including service in World War II. She was operated by two German navies, the Reichsmarine and the Kriegsmarine. Wikipedia

German destroyer Mölders (D186).label: German destroyer Mölders
German destroyer Mölders (D186).description: D186 Mölders was a guided missile destroyer of the Bundesmarine and later the Deutsche Marine. It was the second ship of the Lütjens class, a modification of the Charles F. Adams class. Wikipedia

German cruiser Königsberg.label: German cruiser Königsberg
German cruiser Königsberg.description: Königsberg was a German light cruiser that was operated between 1929 and April 1940, including service in World War II. She was the lead vessel of her class and was operated by two German navies, the Reichsmarine and the Kriegsmarine. Wikipedia

German night fighter direction vessel To.label: German night fighter direction vessel Togo
German night fighter direction vessel To.description: The MS Togo was a German merchant ship that was launched in 1938. Requisitioned by the Kriegsmarine as Schiff 14, in April 1940 she participated in the invasion of Norway; in August 1940 was converted ... Wikipedia

German submarine Deutschland.label: German submarine Deutschland
German submarine Deutschland.description: Deutschland was a blockade-breaking German merchant submarine used during World War I. It was developed with private funds and operated by the North German Lloyd Line. Wikipedia

German submarine U-2511.label: German submarine U-2511
German submarine U-2511.description: German submarine U-2511 was a Type XXI U-boat of Nazi Germany's Kriegsmarine during World War II. The Elektroboote submarine was laid down on 7 July 1944 at the Blohm & Voss yard at Hamburg, launched ... Wikipedia

Golden Hind.label: Golden Hind
Golden Hind.description: Golden Hind or Hinde was an English galleon best known for her circumnavigation of the globe between 1577 and 1580, captained by Sir Francis Drake. Wikipedia

HMAS Nizam (G38).label: HMAS Nizam
HMAS Nizam (G38).description: HMAS Nizam was an N class destroyer of the Royal Australian Navy. The destroyer, named after Sir Osman Ali Khan, the last Nizam of Hyderabad, was commissioned into the RAN in 1940, although the ship ... Wikipedia

HMAS Sydney (1912).label: HMAS Sydney
HMAS Sydney (1912).description: HMAS Sydney was a Chatham class light cruiser of the Royal Australian Navy. Laid down in 1911 and launched in 1912, the cruiser was commissioned into the RAN in 1913. Wikipedia

HMHS Britannic.label: HMHS Britannic
HMHS Britannic.description: HMHS Britannic was the third and largest Olympic-class ocean liner of the White Star Line. She was the sister ship of RMS Olympic and RMS Titanic, and was intended to enter service as the transatlantic passenger liner, RMS Britannic. Wikipedia

HMNZS Achilles (70).label: HMNZS Achilles
HMNZS Achilles (70).description: HMNZS Achilles was a Leander-class light cruiser which served with the Royal New Zealand Navy in the Second World War. She became famous for her part in the Battle of the River Plate, alongside Ajax and Exeter. Wikipedia

HMS Antelope (F170).label: HMS Antelope
HMS Antelope (F170).description: HMS Antelope was a Type 21 frigate of the Royal Navy that participated in the Falklands War. Her keel was laid down 23 March 1971 by Vosper Thornycroft in Woolston, Southampton, England. Wikipedia

HMS Berwick (65).label: HMS Berwick (65)
HMS Berwick (65).description: HMS Berwick (65) was a Royal Navy County class heavy cruiser, of the Kent subclass. She was built by Fairfield Shipbuilding and Engineering Company, with the keel being laid down on 15 September 1924. Wikipedia

HMS Canopus (1897).label: HMS Canopus
HMS Canopus (1897).description: HMS Canopus was a pre-dreadnought battleship of the British Royal Navy and the lead ship of the Canopus class. At the beginning of the First world war she was involved in the search for the German East Asia Squadron of Admiral Graf Spee. Wikipedia

HMS Crescent (1892).label: HMS Crescent
HMS Crescent (1892).description: HMS Crescent was a first class cruiser of the Edgar class. Crescent, and her sister ship Royal Arthur, were built to a slightly modified design and are sometimes considered a separate class. She was built at Portsmouth and launched on 30 March 1892. Wikipedia

HMS Cumberland (57).label: HMS Cumberland
HMS Cumberland (57).description: HMS Cumberland was a County class heavy cruiser of the Royal Navy that saw action during the Second World War. Wikipedia

HMS Devonshire (39).label: HMS Devonshire
HMS Devonshire (39).description: HMS Devonshire was a County-class heavy cruiser of the Royal Navy. Constructed at Devonport Dockyard, she was launched in 1927, and commissioned two years later. Wikipedia

HMS Furious (47).label: HMS Furious
HMS Furious (47).description: HMS Furious was a modified Courageous-class battlecruiser built for the Royal Navy during the First World War. Wikipedia

HMS Hasty (H24).label: HMS Hasty (H24)
HMS Hasty (H24).description: HMS Hasty (H24) was an H-class destroyer built for the Royal Navy during the mid-1930s. She was assigned to the Mediterranean Fleet until the beginning of World War II. Wikipedia

HMS Hermes (95).label: HMS Hermes
HMS Hermes (95).description: HMS Hermes was an aircraft carrier built for the Royal Navy. The ship was begun during World War I and finished after the war ended. Wikipedia

HMS Hood (1891).label: HMS Hood
HMS Hood (1891).description: HMS Hood was a modified Royal Sovereign-class pre-dreadnought battleship built for the Royal Navy in the early 1890s and the last of the eight built. Wikipedia

HMS Hostile (H55).label: HMS Hostile (H55)
HMS Hostile (H55).description: HMS Hostile (H55) was an H-class destroyer built for the Royal Navy in the 1930s. During the Spanish Civil War of 1936–1939 the ship spent considerable time in Spanish waters, enforcing the arms blockade ... Wikipedia

HMS Invincible (R05).label: HMS Invincible
HMS Invincible (R05).description: HMS Invincible was the Royal Navy's lead ship of the three light aircraft carriers in her class. She was launched on 3 May 1977 as the seventh ship to carry the name. Wikipedia

HMS Lion (1910).label: HMS Lion
HMS Lion (1910).description: HMS Lion was a battlecruiser of the Royal Navy, the lead ship of her class, which were nicknamed the "Splendid Cats". They were significant improvements over their predecessors of the Indefatigable class in terms of speed, armament and armour. Wikipedia

HMS London (69).label: HMS London
HMS London (69).description: HMS London was a member of the second group of the County class heavy cruiser of the Royal Navy. She and her sisters; HMS Sussex, Shropshire, and Devonshire differed from the earlier group of Counties, ... Wikipedia

HMS Malaya.label: HMS Malaya
HMS Malaya.description: HMS Malaya was a Queen Elizabeth-class battleship of the British Royal Navy, built by Sir W. G. Armstrong Whitworth and Company at High Walker and launched in March 1915. Wikipedia

HMS Neptune (20).label: HMS Neptune
HMS Neptune (20).description:
HMS Neptune was a Leander-class light cruiser which served with the Royal Navy during World War II.
Neptune was the fourth ship of its class and was the ninth Royal Navy vessel to carry the name. Wikipedia

HMS Queen Elizabeth (R08).label: HMS Queen Elizabeth
HMS Queen Elizabeth (R08).description: HMS Queen Elizabeth will be the lead ship of the Queen Elizabeth-class of aircraft carrier, the largest warships ever built for the Royal Navy and capable of carrying up to forty aircraft. Wikipedia

HMS Ramillies (07).label: HMS Ramillies
HMS Ramillies (07).description: HMS Ramillies was a Revenge-class battleship of the Royal Navy, named after the Battle of Ramillies. The ship is notable for having served in both the First and Second World Wars. Wikipedia

HMS Resolution (1771).label: HMS Resolution
HMS Resolution (1771).description: HMS Resolution was a sloop of the Royal Navy, a converted merchant collier purchased by the Navy and adapted, in which Captain James Cook made his second and third voyages of exploration in the Pacific. Wikipedia

HMS Revenge (06).label: HMS Revenge
HMS Revenge (06).description: HMS Revenge was the lead ship of the Revenge class of battleships of the Royal Navy, the ninth to bear the name. She was launched during World War I in 1915. Wikipedia

HMS Royal Sovereign (05).label: HMS Royal Sovereign
HMS Royal Sovereign (05).description: HMS Royal Sovereign was a Revenge-class battleship of the Royal Navy displacing 28,000 metric tons and armed with eight 15-inch guns in four twin turrets. Wikipedia

HMS Sheffield (D80).label: HMS Sheffield
HMS Sheffield (D80).description: HMS Sheffield was the second Royal Navy ship to be named after the city of Sheffield in Yorkshire. She was a Type 42 Guided Missile Destroyer laid down by Vickers Shipbuilding and Engineering at Barrow-in-Furness on 15 January 1970. Wikipedia

HMS Shropshire (73).label: HMS Shropshire
HMS Shropshire (73).description: HMS Shropshire was a Royal Navy heavy cruiser of the London sub-class of County class cruisers. She is the only warship to have been named after Shropshire, England. Wikipedia

HMS Warspite (03).label: HMS Warspite
HMS Warspite (03).description: HMS Warspite was a Queen Elizabeth-class battleship, the seventh warship of the Royal Navy to carry the name. Her thirty-year career covered both world wars and took her across the Atlantic, Indian, Arctic and Pacific Oceans. Wikipedia

HMS Wivern (1863).label: HMS Wivern
HMS Wivern (1863).description: The first HMS Wivern was an ironclad turret ship built at Birkenhead, England, one of two sister ships secretly ordered from the John Laird Sons & Company shipyard by the Confederate States of America in 1862. Wikipedia

HMT Southland.label: HMT Southland
HMT Southland.description: HMT Southland was an ocean liner launched in July 1900 as SS Vaderland for Red Star Line service between Antwerp and New York. During her passenger career, the ship initially sailed under British registry, but was re-registered in Antwerp in 1903. Wikipedia

Henry Grace à Dieu.label: Henry Grace à Dieu
Henry Grace à Dieu.description: Henry Grace à Dieu, also known as Great Harry, was an English carrack or "great ship" of the 16th century. Contemporary with Mary Rose, Henry Grace à Dieu was even larger. Wikipedia

Huáscar (ironclad).label: Huáscar

INS Lahav.label: INS Lahav
INS Lahav.description: The INS Lahav is a Sa'ar 5-class corvette of the Israeli Navy that was built by Northrop Grumman Ship Systems in 1993. She is one of three Sa'ar 5-class corvettes in service with the Israeli Navy and her homeport is Haifa, Israel. Wikipedia

INS Viraat.label: INS Viraat (R22)
INS Viraat.description: INS Viraat (R22) is a Centaur-class aircraft carrier in service with the Indian Navy. INS Viraat is the flagship of the Indian Navy, the oldest carrier in service and one of three aircraft carriers based in the Indian Ocean Region. Wikipedia

Italian aircraft carrier Giuseppe Gariba.label: Italian aircraft carrier Giuseppe Garibaldi
Italian aircraft carrier Giuseppe Gariba.description: Giuseppe Garibaldi is an Italian aircraft carrier, the first through deck aviation ship ever built for the Italian Navy, and the first Italian ship built to operate fixed-wing aircraft. Wikipedia

Italian aircraft carrier Sparviero.label: Italian aircraft carrier Sparviero
Italian aircraft carrier Sparviero.description: Sparviero was an Italian aircraft carrier designed and built during World War II. She was originally the ocean liner MS Augustus. The conversion was started in 1942 and was almost completed, but the ship was never delivered to the Regia Marina. Wikipedia

Italian battleship Dante Alighieri.label: Italian battleship Dante Alighieri
Italian battleship Dante Alighieri.description: Dante Alighieri was the first dreadnought battleship built for the Regia Marina. Completed in 1913, she was the first battleship built with her main armament in triple-gun turrets. Wikipedia

Italian cruiser Eugenio di Savoia.label: Italian cruiser Eugenio di Savoia
Italian cruiser Eugenio di Savoia.description: Eugenio di Savoia was a Condottieri class light cruiser, which served in the Regia Marina during World War II. She survived the war but was given as a war reparation to the Hellenic Navy in 1947. She was renamed Elli and served until 1964. Wikipedia

Italian cruiser Gorizia.label: Italian cruiser Gorizia
Italian cruiser Gorizia.description: Gorizia was an Italian Zara class heavy cruiser, which served in the Regia Marina during World War II. The ship was named after the city of Gorizia. She was the only surviving cruiser of her class after the Battle of Cape Matapan in 1941. Wikipedia

Italian cruiser Pola.label: Italian cruiser Pola
Italian cruiser Pola.description: The Pola was a Zara class heavy cruiser of the Italian Regia Marina. She was built in the OTO shipyard at Livorno and entered service in 1932. She was sunk in the battle of Cape Matapan during World War II. Wikipedia

Italian cruiser Raimondo Montecuccoli.label: Italian cruiser Raimondo Montecuccoli
Italian cruiser Raimondo Montecuccoli.description: Raimondo Montecuccoli was a Condottieri-class light cruiser serving with the Italian Regia Marina during World War II. She survived the war and served in the post-war Marina Militare until 1964. Wikipedia

Italian cruiser Zara.label: Italian cruiser Zara
Italian cruiser Zara.description: Zara was an Italian Zara class heavy cruiser, which served in the Regia Marina during World War II. The cruiser was named after the Adriatic city of Zara. Wikipedia

Italian training ship Amerigo Vespucci.label: Italian training ship Amerigo Vespucci
Italian training ship Amerigo Vespucci.description: The Amerigo Vespucci is a tall ship of the Marina Militare, named after the explorer Amerigo Vespucci. Its home port is La Spezia, Italy, and it is in use as a school ship. Wikipedia

Japanese aircraft carrier Kaiyo.label: Japanese aircraft carrier Kaiyo
Japanese aircraft carrier Kaiyo.description: Kaiyo was an escort carrier operated by the Imperial Japanese Navy during World War II. The ship was originally built as the ocean liner Argentina Maru. Wikipedia

Japanese cruiser Furutaka.label: Japanese cruiser Furutaka
Japanese cruiser Furutaka.description: IJN Furutaka was the lead ship in the two-vessel Furutaka-class of heavy cruisers in the Imperial Japanese Navy. It was named after Mount Furutaka, located on Etajima, Hiroshima immediately behind the Imperial Japanese Navy Academy. Wikipedia

Japanese cruiser Kinugasa.label: Japanese cruiser Kinugasa
Japanese cruiser Kinugasa.description: IJN Kinugasa was the second vessel in the two-vessel Aoba-class of heavy cruisers in the Imperial Japanese Navy. It was named after Mount Kinugasa, located in Yokosuka, Kanagawa, Japan. Wikipedia

Japanese cruiser Nachi.label: Japanese cruiser Nachi
Japanese cruiser Nachi.description: Nachi was the second of four Myōkō-class heavy cruisers built for the Imperial Japanese Navy — the other ships of the class being Myōkō, Ashigara and Haguro. She was named after a mountain in Wakayama Prefecture. Wikipedia

Japanese cruiser Suzuya (1934).label: Japanese cruiser Suzuya
Japanese cruiser Suzuya (1934).description: Suzuya was the third of four vessels in the Mogami class of heavy cruisers in the Imperial Japanese Navy. She was named after the Suzuya river on Karafuto. Wikipedia

Japanese destroyer Akigumo.label: Japanese destroyer Akigumo
Japanese destroyer Akigumo.description:
Akigumo was an Imperial Japanese Navy destroyer of the Kagerō-class.
Shortly after the Battle of the Santa Cruz Islands during the early hours of 27 October 1942, Akigumo along with the destroyer ... Wikipedia

Japanese destroyer Arashio.label: Japanese destroyer Arashio
Japanese destroyer Arashio.description: Arashio was the fourth of ten Asashio-class destroyers built for the Imperial Japanese Navy in the mid-1930s under the Circle Two Supplementary Naval Expansion Program. Wikipedia

Japanese destroyer Maikaze.label: Japanese destroyer Maikaze
Japanese destroyer Maikaze.description:
Maikaze was a Kagero-class destroyer of the Imperial Japanese Navy.
On 17 February 1944, while evacuating convoys to Yokosuka from Truk following Allied attack on Truk, Maikaze, the cruiser Katori, and ... Wikipedia

Japanese destroyer Niizuki.label: Japanese destroyer Niizuki
Japanese destroyer Niizuki.description:
Niizuki was an Akizuki-class destroyer of the Imperial Japanese Navy.
On the night of 4–5 July 1943, Niizuki led a troop transport run to Kolombangara. Wikipedia

Japanese destroyer Satsuki (1925).label: Japanese destroyer Satsuki
Japanese destroyer Satsuki (1925).description: Satsuki was one of twelve Mutsuki-class destroyers, built for the Imperial Japanese Navy following World War I. Wikipedia

Japanese destroyer Shimakaze (1942).label: Japanese destroyer Shimakaze
Japanese destroyer Shimakaze (1942).description: Shimakaze was a one-off super-destroyer built for the Imperial Japanese Navy during World War II. She was armed with six 127 mm dual purpose guns and conventional anti-aircraft and anti-submarine weaponry. Wikipedia

Japanese seaplane carrier Wakamiya.label: Japanese seaplane carrier Wakamiya
Japanese seaplane carrier Wakamiya.description: Wakamiya was a seaplane carrier of the Imperial Japanese Navy and the first Japanese aircraft carrier. She was converted from a transport ship into a seaplane carrier and commissioned in August 1914. Wikipedia
